<div class="clear"></div>
<div class="left3colsidebar">
<div style="overflow:hidden">
<div class="imageleft">
<img src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/blog-authors/alberto-chimal/chimal-alberto-bio.jpg" alt width height border="1" />
<br/>
<div class="phototagleft">
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Alberto Chimal </strong>is a Mexican author of short stories, novels, and children’s books. In addition to his work as a screenwriter, he is the first Mexican to write a Batman story for DC Comics. He has received national and international awards and is considered a prominent figure of contemporary Latin American literature.</p>
<div class="clear"></div>
<div class="imageleft">
<img src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/translators/george-henson/contrib-george-henson-randy-tunnell.jpg" alt width="150" height="150" border="1" />
<br/>
<div class="phototagleft">
Photo: Randy Tunnell
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>George Henson</strong> is the author of ten book-length translations, including works by Cervantes laureates Sergio Pitol and Elena Poniatowska. His translation of Abel Posse’s <em>A Long Day in Venice</em> was longlisted for the 2023 Queen Sofía Spanish Institute Translation Prize. He is a Tulsa Artist Fellow.</p>
<div class="clear"></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<span class="a2a_kit a2a_kit_size_32 addtoany_list" data-a2a-url="https://www.worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/fiction/north-star-alberto-chimal" data-a2a-title="North Star, by Alberto Chimal"><a class="a2a_button_facebook"></a><a class="a2a_button_twitter"></a><a class="a2a_button_email"></a><a class="a2a_dd addtoany_share" href="https://www.addtoany.com/share#url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.worldliteraturetoday.org%2Fblog%2Ffiction%2Fnorth-star-alberto-chimal&amp;title=North%20Star%2C%20by%20Alberto%20Chimal"></a></span>
